[0m[49m[38;5;10m+       1029[0m:[38;5;10m[49m **Information-blocking compliance posture.** The 21st Century Cures Act information-blocking provisions require that the institution release a patient's records on request, regardless of which name the records were created under. The release pipeline has to recognize the linkage (the matcher's job) and apply the patient's explicit preferences for prior-name display in the released documents (the access-control envelope's job). Build the patient-access-API release path as a deliberate workflow that consults both the linkage and the envelope, with audit logging on every release. Skip this and the institution either over-releases (exposing prior names that the patient preferred to suppress) or under-releases (failing to include records under prior names, which is increasingly characterized as information blocking). 
